messages.content: FancyVideo-ComfyUI is a custom node for FancyVideo, which is a GitHub project by 360CVGroup.
How can you run FancyVideo-ComfyUI online?

FancyVideo-ComfyUI can be run online through a mirror site (https://www.xiangongyun.com/image/detail/2d27f239-c8f9-43f6-9156-fb1c06b6e3df) and there is a tutorial available on Bilibili (https://b23.tv/BMu5AkH).
What information is provided in the example section of FancyVideo-ComfyUI documentation?
The example section of FancyVideo-ComfyUI documentation provides the first frame image, the prompt used, and the resulting output video.
What was the prompt used in the FancyVideo-ComfyUI example?
The prompt used in the FancyVideo-ComfyUI example was 'A cat wearing sunglasses and working as a lifeguard at a pool.'
What is shown in the first frame image of the FancyVideo-ComfyUI example?
The first frame image of the FancyVideo-ComfyUI example shows a cat wearing sunglasses, which is used as the starting point for generating the video based on the given prompt.
What is the source of the output video in the FancyVideo-ComfyUI example?
The output video in the FancyVideo-ComfyUI example is sourced from 'https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/45bda6a4-0244-4218-90ab-0337a731074c'.
Is FancyVideo-ComfyUI a standalone project or an extension of another project?
FancyVideo-ComfyUI is a custom node (extension) for the FancyVideo project on GitHub.
